Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
delete_bump_grid(25.10)                                delete_bump_grid(25.10)

Name
       delete_bump_grid - Removes the bump grid from the design

Syntax
        delete_bump_grid

       [-help]

       [-grid_names string< |> -all ]

       Removes  the  bump grid from the design. Use this command anytime after
       creating a bump grid.

Parameters
       -all   Deletes all the bump grids.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -grid_names <string>
              Specifies the name(s) of the bump grid to be deleted.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each delete_bump_grid parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man delete_bump_grid

Example
              * The  following  command deletes all the bump grids in the cur-
                rent design:

                delete_bump_grid -all

              * The following command deletes the myGridFront_9x9  named  bump
                grid:

                delete_bump_grid -grid_names {myGridFront_9x9}

              * The following command deletes multiple bump girds:

                delete_bump_grid    -grid_names    {myGridFront_9x9    myGrid-
                Front_25x25}

Related Information
